fields.physical_description:
[Box] Black card box with hinged lid. On the lid is the title of the game, along with manufacturing details. The print is in white, and the only alternative colour is the red in the magicians fez.
[Box Insert (A)] Plain rectangular card box insert
[Box Insert (B)] Plain card box insert in a rectangular shape
[Box Insert (C)] Plain card in a largely square shape
[Box Insert (D)] Small rectangle of card, plain on one side and green on the other. The green side has a slight shine to it
[Paper Cover Slip (A)] Pale blue paper with toys pointed onto it, using bold colours. 
[Paper Cover Slip (B)] Pale salmon pink thin paper
[Paper Cover Slip (C)] Paper cover, dark and shiny on one side, and cream and matt on the other. It is two sheets of paper, attached to each other.
[Penny] Copper British pre-decimal penny coin, Britannia on one side and George VI on the other side
[Playing Cards] Five playing cards, the 6 of spades, 7 of clubs, King of spades (red version), 8 of spades and 9 of clubs. They are fixed together to make a rectangle and have a safety pin (which is rusting) attached to them
[Spring] Tarnished metal sring, wider at the base than at the top. The base is covered with a circle of paper, green on one side
[Cone] Folded and glued paper to form a cone, green side facing outwards
[Playing Card] Cream card with two red clubs symbols on one side
[Card trick accessory] White card instruction sheet attached with black elastic to a piece of black card with five diamonds cut into it
[Instruction Booklet (A)] Cream paper printed with black ink
[Instruction Sheets (B)] Paper instruction sheet with black printing
[Membership Requests] Dark blue sugar paper card printed with black ink
[Instruction Leaflet (C)] White card with blue print
[Instruction Leaflet (D)] Dark beige card with black print
[String] Length of cream string, knotted into a loop. 
[Paper clips] Metal curved to form paper clips
[Paper] Scrap of card, printed on one side in black ink. No word is complete due to the nature of the tears
[Circle of card] Circle of card with small length of thin black wire protruding. A woodgrain effect is present on one side of the circle.
[Metal Discs] Metal discs with shallow sides and some moulding in the bases. The outside is painted dark blue.
[Medium Metal Tube] Metal tube painted red on the outside. It was initially a sheet of metal that has been fastened at the seams to make it into a tube. The paint is flaking in some places.
[Large Metal Tube] Large metal tube, painted red on the outside. Initially would have been a sheet of metal, but it has been fastened at the edges to create a tube. The paint is substantially chipped on the outside.
[Small Metal Tube] Small metal tube, painted black on the inside and outside. A tarnished metal hook is attached to the top of the tube, and a thick circle of card is attached to the base of the tube.
[Magic Wand] Thin magic wand, painted black with white on each end. It is hollow, and a sheet of metal has been rolled to achieve this effect
[Fabrics] A bundle of different ribbons and fabrics and papers, exceedingly difficult to unravel.

fields.public_access_description: This Magic Set has a variety of tricks in it, suitable for children. Some of these tricks include 'Magic Ace', 'The Elusive King' and 'Disc Divining'. It also includes the option to become a member of 'The Magic Square'. It was made by Metra in the early 1950s.
